FBIS3-10948 "drlat050_b_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-050 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 Haiti Chamber Vice President: Senate `Serious Obstacle' FL1403210994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 GMT 14 Mar 94 FL1403210994 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio Language: French Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] According to the vice president of the Chamber of Deputies, Deputy Yves Pericles Beauge, the Senate of the Republic is a serious obstacle to any resolution of the crisis. In an interview with Signal FM, Beauge acknowledged that the Senate will need to play a dominant role in achieving a way out of the crisis. He says a modus operandi must be developed to keep the nation from bearing the brunt of divergences among senators. [Begin recording, in Creole] If the situation in the Senate remains as it is -- already a great handicap -- it will continue to prevent a resolution because any and all decisions, even if President Aristide consents to the plan, require that the Senate take certain steps that fall within the scope of its responsibilities. [passage omitted] [end recording]
